---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import Section from "../components/Section.astro";
import HeroCanvas from "../components/HeroCanvas.astro";
import SectionIntro from "../components/SectionIntro.astro";
import StructuralPreview from "../components/StructuralPreview.astro";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout title="Home" description="A companion to Gravity's Rainbow: diagrams, networks, and dissolving structures.">
  <Nav slot="nav" />

  <section class="hero">
    <HeroCanvas />
    <div class="container hero-inner">
      <div class="hero-copy">
        <p class="hero-kicker">Thomas Pynchon · 1973</p>
        <h1>The Zone</h1>
        <p class="hero-subtitle">
          A companion to <em>Gravity's Rainbow</em>: episodes, character networks,
          and dissolving structures, traced through careful computation and reading.
        </p>
        <p class="hero-links">
          <a href={`${base}network/`}>Begin with the network <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
          <span class="hero-or">or</span>
          <a href={`${base}episodes/`}>start from the episodes</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Section id="contents">
    <div class="section-label reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Contents</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal">
      <SectionIntro number="01" title="Episodes" href={`${base}episodes/`}>
        <p>
          Pynchon's novel divides into seventy-three episodes spread unevenly across
          four parts. The shortest runs to a few hundred words; the longest, episode
          3.11, sprawls past sixteen thousand. This section treats the episode as a
          formal unit — measuring scale, sequence, and the structural rhythm of the
          novel's four-part architecture.<sup class="fnref"><a href="#notes">1</a></sup>
        </p>
      </SectionIntro>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal">
      <SectionIntro number="02" title="Dissolution" href={`${base}dissolution/`}>
        <p>
          Tyrone Slothrop, the closest thing the novel has to a protagonist, gradually
          disperses. His name fractures into aliases, his presence thins, and other
          characters fill the space he leaves behind. The dissolution page traces
          these metrics episode by episode: canonical mentions, alias diversity,
          orbit density, and the lengthening runs of absence.
        </p>
      </SectionIntro>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal">
      <SectionIntro number="03" title="Network" href={`${base}network/`}>
        <p>
          One hundred and thirty-eight named characters appear across the seventy-three
          episodes. This section maps their co-presence — who appears alongside whom,
          how often, and in which structural positions — to reveal the shifting social
          geometry of the novel, from the dense clusters of Part&nbsp;I to the scattered
          constellations of Part&nbsp;IV.
        </p>
      </SectionIntro>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal">
      <SectionIntro number="04" title="Strands" href={`${base}strands/`}>
        <p>
          Beyond characters and episodes, the novel organises itself along narrative
          strands — recurring plotlines, thematic threads, and motif systems that weave
          through the text. This section is still being consolidated; it will present
          strand geometry, handoff points, and motif intensity once the underlying
          data contracts are finalised.
        </p>
      </SectionIntro>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section id="data" narrow={true}>
    <div class="data-aside reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">In the data</p>
      <p class="data-note">
        73 episodes, four parts, ~333,000 words. The sparkline below shows each
        episode's word count left to right, grouped by part. Notice Part&nbsp;III's
        expansion — thirty-two episodes, the widest field of structural variation
        in the novel.
      </p>
      <StructuralPreview />
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section id="method" narrow={true}>
    <div class="method-block reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">On method</p>
      <h2>Computational reading, kept answerable to form.</h2>
      <p>
        The Zone is built from structured computational analysis of the text, combined
        with close editorial reading. Character networks are derived from episode-level
        co-presence counts; dissolution metrics track Slothrop's name, aliases, and
        co-character density; strand geometry maps plotline continuity and motif
        recurrence. All visualisations draw on public-safe exports from a larger
        research pipeline,<sup class="fnref"><a href="#notes">2</a></sup> and the
        interpretive layer is kept deliberately restrained — the aim is legibility,
        not argument.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section id="notes" narrow={true}>
    <div class="notes-block reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Notes</p>
      <ol class="notes-list">
        <li>Episode boundaries follow the conventional section breaks marked by the
          square-bracket numbering in most editions. Word counts are derived from a
          normalised plain-text transcription.</li>
        <li>The research pipeline and its full analytical outputs remain in a private
          repository. Only explicitly public-safe, stripped exports are used on this
          site. See <a href="https://github.com/dinghaoluo/the_zone_site">the source
          repository</a> for the provenance log.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</Layout>

<style>
  .hero {
    position: relative;
    padding: var(--space-3xl) 0;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .hero-inner {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .hero-copy {
    max-width: var(--max-width-narrow);
  }

  .hero-kicker {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .hero h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 7vw, 4.5rem);
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2vw, 1.5rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    max-width: 34rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .hero-links {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .hero-links a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .hero-or {
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    margin: 0 0.3em;
  }

  .section-label {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .data-aside {
    padding: var(--space-xl) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
  }

  .data-note {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin: var(--space-md) 0 var(--space-lg);
    max-width: 36rem;
  }

  .method-block h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    margin: var(--space-lg) 0 var(--space-md);
  }

  .method-block p:last-child {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .notes-block {
    padding-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .notes-list {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    padding-left: 1.5em;
    list-style: decimal;
  }

  .notes-list li {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .notes-list li a {
    color: var(--color-accent-dim);
  }

  .notes-list li a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .hero {
      padding: var(--space-2xl) 0;
    }
  }
</style>
